						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Dreamwriter wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I had a lot of fun in this case figuring out the timing of getting the palette reloading with minimal corruption (now I just need to get rid of the scroll corruption on the bottom edge).</div><br />It's worth noting that this is the kind of thing you should test on real hardware. These fine timing details often vary a lot from one emulator to another, so it's better to calibrate them according to the real hardware.<br /><br />That said, the mid-screen scroll change should be easier to get right than the palette change. Since you have rendering disabled for the palette update already, using the $2006/5/5/6 combo and enabling rendering near the start of the next HBlank should do the trick.</div>

